<rss xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" version="2.0"><channel><title>MariaDB Knowledge Base Comments for: Installing MariaDB Binary Tarballs</title><link>https://mariadb.com/kb/en/installing-mariadb-binary-tarballs/+comments/feed/</link><description></description><atom:link href="https://mariadb.com/kb/en/installing-mariadb-binary-tarballs/+comments/feed/" rel="self"></atom:link><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Fri, 23 Dec 2022 06:27:46 +0000</lastBuildDate><item><title>Re: Installing MariaDB Binary Tarballs</title><link>https://mariadb.com/kb/en/installing-mariadb-binary-tarballs/+comments/2543</link><description>&lt;p&gt;You are probably using a configuration file in /etc.
Make sure you have your own configuration file, usually in the mariadb server base directory. For example, if the base directory is /usr/local/mysql, you should execute:
./scripts/mysql_install_db  --basedir=/usr/local/mysql --defaults-file=/usr/local/mysql/my.cnf&lt;/p&gt;
</description><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Ivan Zoratti</dc:creator><guid>https://mariadb.com/kb/en/installing-mariadb-binary-tarballs/+comments/2543</guid></item><item><title>Re: Installing MariaDB Binary Tarballs</title><link>https://mariadb.com/kb/en/installing-mariadb-binary-tarballs/+comments/1874</link><description>&lt;p&gt;Hi,
I have been trying to install &lt;a href="/kb/en/mariadb-1018-release-notes/"&gt;mariadb 10.1.8&lt;/a&gt; from Binary referring this document. But there are no clear cut steps to be followed as I am stumbling upon every step while calling the script mysql_install_db. I am installing this on a clean slate. Am I supposed have / copy any preexisting files to certain directories?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I am getting below error - &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class="fixed"&gt;root@localhost:/usr/local/mysql# ./scripts/mysql_install_db  --basedir=/usr/local/mysql 
Installing MariaDB/MySQL system tables in '/var/lib/mysql' ...
2015-12-08  8:56:59 140556698441600 [Note] /usr/local/mysql/bin/mysqld (mysqld 10.1.8-MariaDB-log) starting as process 26886 ...
2015-12-08  8:56:59 140556698441600 [ERROR] mysqld: File '/var/log/mysql/mariadb-bin.index' not found (Errcode: 2 &amp;#34;No such file or directory&amp;#34;)
2015-12-08  8:56:59 140556698441600 [ERROR] Aborting
&lt;/pre&gt;</description><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">trupti mali</dc:creator><guid>https://mariadb.com/kb/en/installing-mariadb-binary-tarballs/+comments/1874</guid></item><item><title>Check your version of GLIBC</title><link>https://mariadb.com/kb/en/installing-mariadb-binary-tarballs/+comments/981</link><description>&lt;p&gt;To check which version of GLIBC you have installed:
ldd --version&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can also "run" the libaray:
/lib/libc.so.6&lt;/p&gt;
</description><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Adam Scott</dc:creator><guid>https://mariadb.com/kb/en/installing-mariadb-binary-tarballs/+comments/981</guid></item><item><title>Re: Installing MariaDB Binary Tarballs</title><link>https://mariadb.com/kb/en/installing-mariadb-binary-tarballs/+comments/586</link><description>&lt;p&gt;Hi,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;5.1.32 is several years old, it wasn't a GA release and isn't even offered at our &lt;a href="https://downloads.mariadb.org/mariadb/+releases/"&gt;downloads page&lt;/a&gt;. Where did you get the packages and why do you want to install such an ancient version on the newest Ubuntu distribution? &lt;/p&gt;
</description><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Elena Stepanova</dc:creator><guid>https://mariadb.com/kb/en/installing-mariadb-binary-tarballs/+comments/586</guid></item></channel></rss>